'''Wellington Moisés Ramírez Preciado''' (born 9 September 2000) is an Ecuadorian [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Super League Greece]] club [[A.E. Kifisia F.C.|A.E. Kifisia]] and the [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador national team]].

==Club career==
Born in [[Guayaquil]], Ramírez joined [[C.S.D. Independiente del Valle]]'s youth setup in 2016, from Toreros. He made his first team debut at the age of just 17 on 10 July 2018, starting in a 1–3 away loss against [[S.D. Aucas]].

On 30 January 2019, Ramírez moved abroad and joined [[Real Sociedad]] on loan until June; he was initially assigned to [[Real Sociedad B|the reserves]] in [[Segunda División B]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realsociedad.eus/es/noticias/detalle/refuerzo-para-la-porteria-del-sanse|title=Refuerzo para la portería del Sanse|trans-title=Addition to the goal of ''Sanse''|publisher=Real Sociedad|language=es|date=30 January 2019|accessdate=20 September 2020}}</ref> His loan was extended until 31 December on 28 June, with a buyout clause,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realsociedad.eus/es/noticias/detalle/ampliada-su-cesion|title=Ampliada su cesión|trans-title=Loan extended|publisher=Real Sociedad|language=es|date=28 June 2019|accessdate=20 September 2020}}</ref> which was declined on 10 December.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realsociedad.eus/en/news/details/real-decline-ramirez-buy-out-option|title=Real decline Ramírez buy-out option|publisher=Real Sociedad|date=10 December 2019|accessdate=20 September 2020}}</ref>

Upon returning, Ramírez was assigned back at the main squad, being mainly a backup to [[Jorge Pinos]].

==International career==
He made his debut for the [[Ecuador national football team]] on 7 October 2021 in a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|World Cup qualifier]] against [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[FIFA]]|url=https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/mens/worldcup/qatar2022/qualifiers/conmebol/match-center/400104609|title=Ecuador v Bolivia game report|date=7 October 2021}}</ref>

Ramírez was named in the Ecuadorian squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite tweet |author=Ecuador national football team |author-link=Ecuador national football team |user=LaTri |number=1592288685797494784 |date=14 November 2022 |title=Aquí están los 26 jugadores elegidos por el DT Gustavo Alfaro para jugar la Copa Mundial FIFA, estamos listos para hacer historia |trans-title=Here are the 26 players chosen by head coach Gustavo Alfaro to play the FIFA World Cup, we are ready to make history. |language=es |access-date=14 November 2022}}</ref>

Ramírez was called up to the final 26-man Ecuador squad for the [[2024 Copa América]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eluniverso.com/deportes/futbol/ecuador-presenta-lista-oficial-para-la-copa-america-gonzalo-plata-y-robert-arboleda-quedaron-relegados-nota/|title=Ecuador presenta lista oficial para la Copa América: Gonzalo Plata y Robert Arboleda quedaron relegados|trans-title=Ecuador presents official roster for Copa America: Gonzalo Plata and Robert Arboleda left off the list|publisher=[[El Universo]]|date=29 May 2024|language=es}}</ref>

